A Port Elizabeth man convicted for the possession of child pornography was sentenced yesterday to an effective eight years in prison. Dylan Gouws, 23, of Charlo, was arrested for taking pictures of naked children in March last year. Police found images of naked boys, aged 5 and 6, on his camera, as well as explicit comics on his hard drive. He was charged with four counts related to the creation and possession of child pornography. He admitted guilt in September. In the Port Elizabeth Magistrate s Court yesterday, magistrate Thandeka Mashiyi said one of her main concerns when considering Gouws s punishment was public interest and the safety of the community. She also referred to the increasing exploitation of children in the digital age. Related Share on Facebook Share Share on Twitter Tweet Share on Google Plus Share